race.description: Boxing Day Races 26Th December Maiden Plate
race.comment: RING MY BELL (11) gets her chance to break though in a mediocre maiden. Loomed up on the corner but failed to go on with the job last start over this distance at Muswellbrook. On a quick back-up and the tongue tie going on might be important. Has the ability to stretch this field. GO RUSSIAN (9) ran a nice race two back over 900m then got a long way back before passing a few in the straight over today's journey at Scone last time out. Freshened up and if she can slot in from the wide gate is a winning hope. CASDAEMON (1) weakened in the concluding stages when returning from a long spell at Moree recently. Should come on from that run and offer a bit more at the finish this time. CALPIN'S MELODY (5) is a first starter from the Gavin Groth stable. Has trialled once recently and did a fair job at Tamworth. Worth a watch for market support. ACIRA (4) has switched stables and is first-up after an eight-month break. Has a host of gear changes so might be one to monitor.
